Cicindela dongalensis imperatrix

).

A genus widespread throughout the Oriental, Palaearctic and Afrotropical Regions. Most of its subgenera and species occur in Africa, which is most likely the centre of origin of the genus. The Afrotropical species of this genus were revised by Rivalier (
1958
), but with the subsequent description of more subgenera and species/ subspecies a new revision is needed.

